Intended for high school students, future transfer students, and parents.

I’m a California native who transferred to UCLA during my sophomore year from the University of Utah. With the school year and application season around the corner, I hope sharing my lived experiences gives guidance to prospective Bruins! (Or helps you realize UCLA isn’t for you)

UCLA has been ranked the number one best public university for five straight years by U.S. News & World Report. Nestled in Westwood, UCLA is in a college town about 35 minutes away from Downtown Los Angeles. It almost has a suburban vibe, but oblivious LA drivers still crowd every neighboring street. On-campus parking is ridiculously limited and expensive, so most of us relied on Uber and Lyft to get out of Westwood.

